https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/w6n9ioqm4vgxnkkAfsbJLmb8RDD.jpg A disturbing chapter in Russian history is explored in this documentary. In 1933, Joseph Stalin sent 6000 "unwanted" citizens of Moscow and Leningrad to a desolate Siberian island - with no food or clothes to speak of. Decades later this documentary returns to the island.
